docs.abstract: She’s run the I.M.F. She’s a lawyer. She’s not an economist. Does that matter as she prepares to lead the European Central Bank?
docs.snippet: She’s run the I.M.F. She’s a lawyer. She’s not an economist. Does that matter as she prepares to lead the European Central Bank?
docs.lead_paragraph: She doesn’t have the typical résumé — no doctorate in economics, no post as a central banker — for running the body that sets monetary policy for one-fifth of the global economy. But investors are betting that Christine Lagarde, the surprise nominee to be the next president of the European Central Bank, will act in much the same way as the bank’s last leader.

headline.main: Christine Lagarde Faces a New Challenge in Europe
headline.print_headline: As Growth Sputters in the Eurozone,  Its Incoming Leader Faces a Challenge
